huntBios.GENERAL_INFORMATION:
This is a new Limited Entry muzzleloader only late buck hunt on a General Season hunt unit (not a trophy unit). This hunt is almost entirely private property.
Do not apply for this hunt unless you have written permission to hunt private property within the boundary. The purpose of this hunt is to reduce mature buck density in an area with high prevalence of Chronic Wasting Disease (CWD). This hunt is primarily an agricultural area hunt.
Hunters should be aware of the Ute Tribal Lands and learn the boundaries. Public hunting is not permitted on Tribal Lands.
huntBios.SAFETY_CONS: This hunt is primarily an agricultural area hunt. Extreme caution must be used to avoid shooting toward houses, agricultural structures or livestock.
huntBios.WEATHER_CONS: The weather on this hunt can vary dramatically during the hunting season. Be prepared for rain, lightening, snow, wind and heat. Fall snow storms occur regularly in this area during this hunt. Most years the snow will melt off within a day or two. Be prepared for dry or muddy conditions.
huntBios.BIOLOGIST_NOTES:
This hunt is intended to target mature bucks early in the rut in a private property area with high buck to doe ratios that has a high prevalence of Chronic Wasting Disease (CWD). The intent is to reduce the potential for mature bucks that may have CWD from dispersing into surrounding areas and spreading CWD. It's been found in other states that in areas with high buck to doe ratios older bucks are more likely to disperse to sounding areas during the rut and thereby spread CWD.
Private landowners are not required to allow public access to hunt on their property. Hunters wanting to hunt this hunt must have written permission to hunt before applying. Obtaining permission after drawing the permit will be very difficult.

huntMaster.SPECIAL_INSTRUCTIONS: This hunt is comprised mostly of private land, hunters are encouraged to obtain written permission from landowners before applying for this hunt.
huntMaster.SPECIAL_PROVISIONS: This is a Limited-entry hunt that takes place on a General-season unit. You will lose your bonus points if you draw out for this hunt.
huntMaster.NOTES:
Baiting big game for the purposes of hunting is now illegal in Utah.
Click here for more information.

The use of all trail cameras (including both non-handheld transmitting and non-transmitting devices) in the harvest or to aid in the harvest of big game is prohibited between July 31 and Dec. 31. Click here for more information.
huntMaster.HARVEST_REPORTING: REQUIRED: click here or call 1-800-221-0659 to report your harvest. You must report your harvest, even if you did not take an animal, within 30 days of the season end date that is printed on your permit; failure to do so may result in you not being able to apply for big game species in subsequent years. Submitting teeth or other biological samples from your animal, or having your animal checked by a DWR representative or CWMU operator does NOT fulfill your mandatory harvest reporting requirement.

huntBoundaryInfos.LAND_OWNERSHIP: This unit is almost entirely private property.  Obtain written permission before applying.
huntBoundaryInfos.WMA_IN_UNIT: The Kevin Conway Wildlife Management Area is included in this hunt but is managed primarily for upland game with very little big game use on the WMA.
huntBoundaryInfos.CAMPGRND_INFO: There are no public campgrounds on this hunt unit. Public camping is permitted on BLM and US Forest Service lands in the area.
huntBoundaryInfos.PRIM_ACCESS_PTS: State Highway 40 accesses the NW portion of the hunt unit.  County roads provide access throughout the hunt unit.
huntBoundaryInfos.SUGGESTED_MAPS:
USGS 1:100,000 Vernal and Duchesne topo maps
Access to OnXmaps or similar product is recommended to show property ownership.
huntBoundaryInfos.ATV_VEH_ACCESS: Only street legal ATVs are allowed on county roads within the hunt unit.  Private property owners control ATV use on their private property.
huntBoundaryInfos.PRIV_TRIBE_LAND_ISSUES: The lands inside this hunt boundary are almost entirely private property or are Ute Tribal trust lands. You must obtain written permission from private landowners to hunt private lands. Ute Tribal lands are excluded from this hunt. Hunting licenses and permits issued by the State of Utah are not valid on Ute Tribal lands.
